  "ciliary_role": "Component of IFT complex B. Essential for anterograde complex integrity, biosynthesis and mainte nce of cilia. Regulation of ciliogenesis and cilia length, it also plays a role as a docking site for complex B proteins attaching to the transition fibres of the basal bodies and is required for localization of the IFT-B complex proteins (27466190). Recruits and interacts with IFT46 to assembly a subcomplex which is a prerequisite for the assembly of IFT-B1, it is also required to localise IFT46 to the basal body (28302912).",
